{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18c70499-1a98-450a-8947-fbec87daaeff","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or** if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.visualstudio` v3+ which includes MTP support — but the recommended path is upgrading to **xUnit v3**.\n\n   For xUnit v3 with MTP:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Update test code** for xUnit v3 breaking changes (if upgrading):\n   - `Assert.Equal` on collections may need lambda syntax changes.\n   - `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` remain the same.\n   - Some Assert overloads were removed/changed.\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key benefit**: MTP makes each test project a standalone executable, enabling faster startup, better parallelism, and `dotnet run` support.\n\nWould you like help with any specific step of the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92df7048-11ab-4b64-902d-2d214bbc0b34","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":457,"requestId":"7038:83273:E1AD21D:F7D45B6:69F2A7CB"},"id":"3cda6b5c-6900-441a-bc37-6c1a29dc1a5d","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:52:37.426Z","parentId":"76444d05-ad28-4a16-8a0f-5915cbadbccf"}
